### Test Authentication Endpoints

### 1. Register a new user
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "TestPassword123!"
}

### 2. Login with the created user
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "password": "TestPassword123!"
}

### 3. Get current user info (replace TOKEN_HERE with actual token from login)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Logout (replace TOKEN_HERE with actual token from login)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN_HERE

### 5. Test registration with invalid data
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "ab",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "password": "weak"
}

### 6. Test login with invalid credentials
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "nonexistent",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

